Vets who hate the protesters have misplaced their anger from the people, and the government, responsible for their being sent to Nam in the first place on to the protesters.  Jane Fonda wasn't responsible for me being there.  The US government put me there. <br><br>
 I enlisted (1968, USMC) and went willingly (69-70)  because I was doing my duty as I had  been taught  but I didn't give up my right to judge the reasons for starting and continuing the war against the Vietnamese people.  I'll never get over the fact that my own government was, no make that is willing to Kill me or my friends and brothers or millions of Vietnamese for only the vaguest of ideas, with almost no strategy for winning the war while big wealthy defense companies  made billions .  If the cause is just and the need is great I would have once obeyed the call but  when I know I will be lied to and used to make someone else rich I say no more<br><br>
 I wasn't spit on but I wouldnt go out of my way let people know I was a vet.  That was more because I got sick of the stupid questions about how many people I had shot than any fear of protesters spit.  
